<span id="freeTextContainer2043661266841222354">I remember reading this book as a young elementary school student and couldn&apos;t remember anything about it so thought it was worth a revisit. This is a very short epistolary book following Leigh Botts who is writing to his favorite author Mr. Henshaw. He tells him all about his family issues and hopes and dreams for his relationship with his dad. It is a sweet novel, but I can&apos;t say I will remember it anymore in 10 years than I did before I read it this year?<br/><br/>De Liver<br/>De Letter<br/>De Sooner<br/>De Better<br/>De </span>
  <span id="freeText2043661266841222354" style="display:none">I remember reading this book as a young elementary school student and couldn't remember anything about it so thought it was worth a revisit. This is a very short epistolary book following Leigh Botts who is writing to his favorite author Mr. Henshaw. He tells him all about his family issues and hopes and dreams for his relationship with his dad. It is a sweet novel, but I can't say I will remember it anymore in 10 years than I did before I read it this year?<br /><br />De Liver<br />De Letter<br />De Sooner<br />De Better<br />De Later<br />De Letter<br />De Madder<br />I Getter</span>
