<div id="review_3039832245" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3039832245" />
    <a title="Jordan Henrichs" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/3427342-jordan-henrichs"><img alt="Jordan Henrichs" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1481522482p2/3427342.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3039832245?book_show_action=true">Dec 04, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jordan Henrichs" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jordan Henrichs" href="/user/show/3427342-jordan-henrichs">Jordan Henrichs</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3039832245" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer15842220593688075931">Perfect book to teach inferring to young readers. Cleary says so much about Leigh without explicitly saying it in his early letters to Henshaw. The growth and change in him as the letters turn into a journal is evident to growing readers. Leigh&apos;s story is a sad one, but one many of my students can relate to even today, making the book somewhat timeless. </span>
  <span id="freeText15842220593688075931" style="display:none">Perfect book to teach inferring to young readers. Cleary says so much about Leigh without explicitly saying it in his early letters to Henshaw. The growth and change in him as the letters turn into a journal is evident to growing readers. Leigh's story is a sad one, but one many of my students can relate to even today, making the book somewhat timeless. </span>
  <a data-text-id="15842220593688075931" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


